docs.abstract: Bristol was built with money from the slave trader Edward Colston. Tearing down his statue has reopened a painful reckoning with the city’s racist past.
docs.snippet: Bristol was built with money from the slave trader Edward Colston. Tearing down his statue has reopened a painful reckoning with the city’s racist past.
docs.lead_paragraph: BRISTOL, England — Standing beneath an empty stone plinth, from which the statue of the 17th-century slave trader Edward Colston was toppled last week, Richard Saunders showed his son photos of three black Americans who had been killed by the police an ocean away and 200 years after the end of Bristol’s slave trade.

headline.main: In an English City, an Early Benefactor Is Now ‘a Toxic Brand’
headline.print_headline: A City Built by an Enslaver Confronts Its Racist History

docs.abstract: Gérald Darmanin, France’s interior minister, said an assailant had stabbed an officer in Cannes. The motive for the attack was not immediately clear.

docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — A French police officer was attacked and stabbed as he sat in his patrol car early Monday morning in the city of Cannes, on the French Riviera, according to the French authorities.

headline.print_headline: Police Officer Is Attacked With a Knife In Cannes

docs.abstract: Can the self-serving political elites address the demands of radicalized and disaffected citizens?
docs.snippet: Can the self-serving political elites address the demands of radicalized and disaffected citizens?
docs.lead_paragraph: SANTIAGO, Chile — In October, a rise in Santiago’s metro fares set off the biggest protests in Chile since the end of Augusto Pinochet’s dictatorship. Protesters were calling out elite corruption, inequality, high prices and low wages, and specifically the pain caused by a privatized retirement system, which left many old people in grinding poverty.

headline.main: The Challenge for Chile and the World

docs.lead_paragraph: NASHVILLE — Kyler Murray completed his unlikely transformation on Thursday night, evolving in less than a year from a college backup planning a career in baseball to a Heisman Trophy-winning No. 1 overall pick in the N.F.L. draft and a prospective franchise quarterback for the Arizona Cardinals.

headline.main: Kyler Murray Makes N.F.L. Draft History at No. 1

docs.lead_paragraph: The family of Anthony Weber, a Los Angeles teenager who was shot and killed last year after being chased by two sheriff’s deputies, will receive $3.75 million under a settlement that county officials approved this week.

docs.abstract: Tired “tough on crime” rhetoric is not the solution to crime in 2022.
docs.snippet: Tired “tough on crime” rhetoric is not the solution to crime in 2022.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mayor Eric Adams of New York City understands the assignment: to keep the nation’s largest city safe amid an alarming rise in violent crime. At least 40 of the people shot so far this year in New York were children and teenagers, or one in every 10 shooting victims. One of those children, Kade Lewin, 12, was shot and killed while sitting with relatives in a parked car in Brooklyn.

headline.main: Mayor Eric Adams Is Stuck on Ideas From 1994 for Crime in 2022
headline.print_headline: On Crime, Adams Is Stuck in 1994

docs.abstract: The London police commissioner apologized to the track star Bianca Williams and her partner after they were handcuffed during a traffic stop on Saturday.
docs.snippet: The London police commissioner apologized to the track star Bianca Williams and her partner after they were handcuffed during a traffic stop on Saturday.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The head of the London Metropolitan Police said on Wednesday that the force’s handcuffing practices would be reviewed, after officers on Saturday pulled a top British sprinter and her partner from their car and handcuffed them in front of their 3-month-old son.

headline.main: London Police to Review Handcuffing Procedures After Detention of Black Athletes
headline.print_headline: London Police Apologize for Handcuffing 2 Black Track Stars
